:17:"www.pinterest.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:69:{i:0;s:54:"Generally speaking standard sizes for door widths are.";i:1;s:62:"8 feet 9 feet 10 feet 12 feet 15 feet 16 feet 18 feet 20 feet.";i:2;s:67:"Your options in garage door sizes also include various thicknesses.";i:3;s:78:"The most economical choice is a steel garage door that is about 18 inch thick.";i:4;s:75:"As you might expect this door also provides the least amount of insulation.";i:5;s:107:"An insulated steel door is made with a ¼ to ½ inch piece of foam insulation inside the thin steel panels.";i:6;s:78:"4 rows Standard garage doors usually have the sizes of 8 x 7 9 x 7 and 10 x 7.";i:7;s:32:"What Size Garage Door Do I Need.";i:8;s:94:"The average garage door size can vary but a typical single-car garage door is 8 x 7 or 9 by 7.";i:9;s:48:"A two-car garage door size is typically 16 by 7.";i:10;s:55:"We install a variety of garage doors sizes in Maryland.";i:11;s:38:"The most common widths we install are.";i:12;s:17:"15 feet 6 inches.";i:13;s:32:"Buying Custom Garage Door Sizes.";i:14;s:36:"Standard Clopay garage door heights.";i:15;s:138:"Standard off the shelf doors are available in 8 feet x 7 feet 9 feet x 7 feet and 10 feet x 7 feet with a taller 8-foot variety available.";i:16;s:115:"Single garage door sizes should be wide enough to accommodate any car type and still have enough space for storage.";i:17;s:212:"Single garage doors can be small enough for golf carts or large enough for tractors depending on your home or community For most homes the standard single-car garage door is 8 to 9 feet wide and 7 to 8 feet high.";i:18;s:101:"New construction frequently offers 9 x 7 garage doors but increasingly offers door widths of 10 feet.";i:19;s:86:"These garage door dimensions tend to be the same for an attached as a detached garage.";i:20;s:24:"Single Garage Door Size.";i:21;s:59:"A standard single garage door is 2100mm high x 2400mm wide.";i:22;s:24:"Double Garage Door Size.";i:23;s:59:"A standard double garage door is 2100mm high x 4800mm wide.";i:24;s:91:"The process of deciding on which type of garage door will best suit your garage carport or.";i:25;s:84:"The standard garage door width and height can vary by where you live but is usually.";i:26;s:86:"8 feet wide by 7 feet tall or 9 feet wide by 7 feet tall for a single car garage door.";i:27;s:43:"16 feet by 7 feet for a double garage door.";i:28;s:97:"Side-hinged garage doors can be purchased in pre-hung steel frames or fit into existing openings.";i:29;s:56:"They can also be automated with special conversion arms.";i:30;s:39:"Tilt-UpUp and Over Canopy Garage Doors.";i:31;s:108:"Like side-hinged styles the tilt-up canopy garage doors dont have sections - theyre made of one solid piece.";i:32;s:173:"If door is fitted between the brickwork a minimum of 10mm clearance over the width and 5mm over the height should be added to the overall frame size when selecting the door.";i:33;s:26:"Overall frame sizes shown.";i:34;s:26:"Overall frame sizes shown.";i:35;s:26:"Frame kit for double door.";i:36;s:243:"On either side of the door leave a minimum 150 mm to fit the garage door hardware as door is always wider than opening 250 mm minimum is recommended If headroomlintel height is a problem there are various restricted headroom options available.";i:37;s:58:"Contact us and a Sales Consultant will happily advice you.";i:38;s:91:"A single-car garage door ranges in size from about 8-9 feet in width to 7-8 feet in height.";i:39;s:84:"This is also a good choice if you dont also use your garage for significant storage.";i:40;s:128:"Should you need more space for your vehicles but still want to keep single doors you can always opt for two single garage doors.";i:41;s:92:"There is a wide variation of door sizes available and sizes will vary between manufacturers.";i:42;s:88:"However here are some of the more popular sizes for the different types of garage doors.";i:43;s:42:"Sizes of Steel and Aluminium Garage Doors.";i:44;s:122: